<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 472px 18px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss"> Strategic Goal</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><div style="font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;">
<!-- OIR: Intro card --><div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#fbfdff;padding:18px 18px 16px 18px;">
<div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:800;color:#5b6b88;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">Organizational Information Requirements (OIR)</div>
<div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:14px;background:#ffffff;padding:14px 16px;margin-top:10px;">
<div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:900;color:#5b6b88;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">Goal statement</div>
<div style="color:#1c2430;font-weight:900;line-height:1.5;font-size:15px;">“Capture the information required for long-term maintenance and operation of the building, ensuring all assets, systems, and spatial data are accurate, complete, and usable throughout the asset lifecycle.”</div>
<div style="margin-top:10px;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">The Organizational Information Requirements (OIR) explain <strong style="color:#1c2430;">why</strong> the organization needs information. They translate business, operational, and asset management goals into clear information needs that inform project-level requirements.</div>
<div style="margin-top:8px;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">These OIRs provide the strategic context for the EIR and ensure that information delivered during the project supports real operational outcomes after handover.</div>
</div>
<div style="margin-top:12px;padding:12px 14px;background:#ffffff;border:1px dashed #cfe1ff;border-radius:16px;color:#1c2430;font-weight:900;">Your role - use these OIR themes to ensure the EIR stays focused on what the Owner actually needs.</div>
</div>
<!-- OIR themes --><div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:16px 18px;">
<h3 style="margin:0 0 12px;font-weight:900;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:#1c2430;font-size:18px;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(14, 30, 61);">OIR themes</span></h3>
<div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,minmax(0,1fr));gap:12px;">
<!-- Portfolio planning --><div style="background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #edf2f8;border-radius:18px;padding:14px;">
<div style="font-weight:900;color:#1c2430;letter-spacing:-.01em;margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="color: rgb(14, 30, 61);">Portfolio planning</span></div>
<ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;color:#5b6b88;font-size:14px;line-height:1.75;">
<li>Statutory approvals</li>
<li>Maintenance planning</li>
<li>Operational oversight</li>
<li>Space utilization</li>
<li>Portfolio modifications</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Asset management --><div style="background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #edf2f8;border-radius:18px;padding:14px;">
<div style="font-weight:900;color:#1c2430;letter-spacing:-.01em;margin-bottom:8px;">Asset management</div>
<ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;color:#5b6b88;font-size:14px;line-height:1.75;">
<li>Asset registration</li>
<li>Life cycle cost information</li>
<li>Risk assessment data</li>
<li>Asset replacement planning</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Business operation --><div style="background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #edf2f8;border-radius:18px;padding:14px;">
<div style="font-weight:900;color:#1c2430;letter-spacing:-.01em;margin-bottom:8px;">Business operation</div>
<ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;color:#5b6b88;font-size:14px;line-height:1.75;">
<li>Health and safety</li>
<li>Environmental performance</li>
<li>Sustainability</li>
<li>Capital investment</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Information needs summary --><div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:16px 18px;">
<h3 style="margin:0 0 12px;font-weight:900;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:#1c2430;font-size:18px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Information needs summary</span></h3>
<table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; height: 169px;" data-pasted="true">
